  "prompt": "Is there an app that gives you recipes based on what you have in the fridge?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several apps that can help you find recipes based on the ingredients you have in your fridge. Some popular options include:\n\n1. **SuperCook**: You simply enter the ingredients you have on hand, and SuperCook will generate a list of recipes you can make.\n\n2. **MyFridgeFood**: This app allows you to check off items in your fridge and pantry and then provides recipes that incorporate those ingredients.\n\n3. **Cookpad**: Cookpad lets you search for recipes by ingredients and also allows you to follow other home cooks for inspiration.\n\n4. **Epicurious**: While primarily a recipe app, Epicurious has a feature that lets you find recipes by ingredient.\n\n5. **Cheftap**: This app also allows you to enter ingredients to find suitable recipes.\n\nThese apps are designed to minimize waste and make meal planning more convenient by using what you already have available.",
